<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1437,554,764]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
This species is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[568,659,597,623]" name="Algeria" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[669,778,597,623]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[787,854,597,623]" name="Spain" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Spain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[907,976,597,623]" name="Israel" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Israel</collectingCountry>
. Its 
<typeStatus box="[1020,1073,597,623]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
, however, is lost so we couldn’t examine it. Only a few characters were found in the literature: body black; body surface polished; head with surface coriaceous, sparsely punctate; eye setose; mesosoma with mesonotum shorter than pronotum; parapsidal signum deep; mesoscutellum as long as mesoscutum; propodeum without posterior spine; forewing bi-banded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
